y%2C%20or%20letting%20them%20see%20your%20children%20but%20not%20leaving%20them%20in%20their%20custody%20overnight.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20all%20or%20nothing%2C%26quot%3B%20Epstein%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAccept%20any%20feelings%20of%20loss%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20might%20have%20a%20dream%20for%20how%20our%20relationship%20with%20our%20parents%20will%20be%20and%20what%20it%20might%20be%20like%20to%20have%20a%20really%20fun%2C%20mutual%20adult%20relationship%20%E2%80%94%20and%20to%20find%20that%20your%20parents%20can't%20offer%20you%20that%20is%20a%20loss.%20There's%20not%20been%20a%20death%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20loss%20of%20a%20world%20you%20envisioned%20you%20might%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20Epstein%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20best%20way%20to%20deal%20with%20that%20feeling%20is%20to%20make%20room%20for%20it%20and%20process%20it%20like%20you%20would%20with%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fstages-of-grief%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etypes%20of%20grief%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20she%20said%2C%20you%20can%20lean%20on%20others%20to%20fill%20the%20roles%20you%20hoped%20your%20parents%20would%20and%20instead%20look%20for%20other%20ways%20to%20build%20connections%20with%20your%20parents%20that%20are%20more%20aligned%20with%20what%20they%20%3Cem%3Ecan%3C%2Fem%3E%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESet%20firm%20boundaries%20and%20stick%20to%20them%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWrite%20a%20list%20of%20what%20you%20are%20and%20aren't%20happy%20to%20talk%20about%20with%20your%20parents%20and%20stick%20to%20that%20list%2C%20Epstein%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteer%20conversations%20toward%20topics%20you%20know%20you're%20happy%20to%20broach%20and%20let%20them%20know%20you%20won't%20be%20engaging%20in%20others%20you%20aren't%20comfortable%20with%2C%20such%20as%20politics%2C%20weight%2C%20or%20child-rearing%2C%20Epstein%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20they%20bring%