20The%20trade-off%20is%20that%20you'll%20have%20a%20higher%20rate%20than%20you%20would%20with%20shorter%20terms%20or%20adjustable%20rates.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E15-Year%20Fixed%20Mortgage%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAverage%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2F15-year-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3E15-year%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%206.22%25%20last%20week%2C%20according%20to%20Freddie%20Mac%20data%2C%20which%20is%20a%20four-basis-point%20decrease%20from%20the%20previous%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20the%20predictability%20that%20comes%20with%20a%20fixed%20rate%20but%20are%20looking%20to%20spend%20less%20on%20interest%20over%20the%20life%20of%20your%20loan%2C%20a%2015-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%20might%20be%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20you.%20Because%20these%20terms%20are%20shorter%20and%20have%20lower%20rates%20than%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgages%2C%20you%20could%20potentially%20save%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20interest.%20However%2C%20you'll%20have%20a%20higher%20monthly%20payment%20than%20you%20would%20with%20a%20longer%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAre%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Going%20Down%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20increased%20throughout%20most%20of%202023.%20But%20mortgage%20rates%20are%20expected%20to%20trend%20down%20in%20the%20coming%20months%20and%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%2012%20months%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-cpi-consumer-price-index-food-gas-housing-prices-february-2024-3%5C%22%3Ethe%20Consumer%20Price%20Index%20rose%20by%203.2%25%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20inflation%20comes%20down%20and%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20is%20able%20to%20start%20cutting%20the%20federal%20funds%20rate%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20should%20fall%20further%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20homeowners%20looking%20to%C2%A0leverage%20their%20home's%20value%C2%A0to%20cover%20a%20big%20purchase%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20a%20home