ps%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdollar-tree-closes-1000-family-dollar-stores-nightmare-acquisition-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710409101000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6567652dc58b6f84123b5b9c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdollar-tree-closes-1000-family-dollar-stores-nightmare-acquisition-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dollar%20Tree%20said%20it%20will%20close%20nearly%201%2C000%20Family%20Dollar%20locations%20over%20the%20next%20three%20years.%20A%20large%20portion%20of%20these%20will%20close%20imminently.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Mary%20Hanbury)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A22%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdollar-tree-closes-1000-family-dollar-stores-nightmare-acquisition-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ambition%20was%20my%20friend.%20Then%20it%20turned%20on%20me.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Illustration%20of%20a%20person%20being%20overwhelmed%20by%20the%20phones.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ef5be790413ab8e1db7c75%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMy%20ambition%20helped%20me%20get%20into%20a%20great%20college%2C%20start%20a%20successful%20newsletter%2C%20and%20do%20a%20fellowship%20at%20Oxford.%20But%20it%20came%20with%20a%20cost.%3Cp%3ESophi%20Gullbrants%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20muggy%20night%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202021%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20livestreaming%20a%20panic%20attack%20on%20Instagram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20tired%20of%20doomscrolling%20through%20pandemic%20news%20and%20thought%20I'd%20take%20my%20mind%20off%20it%20by%20practicing%20my%20promotional%20spiel%20for%20my%20newly%20launched%20mental-health%20newsletter.%20It%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20bad%20idea.%20As%20viewers%20trickled%20in%2C%20I%20noticed%20the%20ominous%20hum%20of%20anxiety%20in%20my%20chest%20that%20I've%20grown%20familiar%20with%20over%20years%20of%20living%20with%20generalized%20anxiety%20disorder.%20Within%20seconds%20I%20was%20spiraling%2C%20sweating%2C%20and%20struggling%20to%20breathe%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I%20kept%20the%20camera%20on.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20what%20a%20panic%20attack%20looks%20like%2C%20folks%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20stammered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20haze%20slowly%20lifted%2C%20I%20felt%20ashamed.%20%3Cem%3EWhat%20was%20I%20thinking%2C%20being%20so%20pathetic%20in%20front%20of%20strangers%3F%20Why%20didn't%20I%20just%20stop%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%20Then%20someone%20commented%2C%20%26quot%3BHearing%20you%20speak%20right%20now%20is%20bliss!%26quot%3B%20The%20flutter%20of%20heart%20emojis%20on%20my%20screen%20consoled%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20dawned%20on%20me%20that%20my%20unfiltered%20performance%20had%20inadvertently%20served%20my%20original%20plan%3A%20building%20my%20brand%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Bauthentic%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bvulnerable%26quot%3B%20mental-health%20storyteller%20to%20attract%20more%20readers%20to%20my%20newsletter.%20It's%20still%20not%20easy%20for%20me%20to%20admit%20it%2C%20but%20that%20night%20I%20used%20my%20pain%20to%20feed%20my%20professional%20ambition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20previous%20job%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fpulse%2Fliving-anxiety-depression-what-has-taught-me-myself-tanmoy-goswami%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eburnout%3C%2Fa%3E%20nearly%20killed%20me%2C%20and%20I%20vowed%20to%20never%20let%20ambition%20swallow%20me%20again.%20Then%20came%20the%20pandemic.%20The%20media%20startup%20I%20was%20working%20at%20shut%20down%2C%20and%20my%2015-year%20career%20imploded%20overnight.%20In%20a%20desperate%20attempt%20to%20cobble%20together%20an%20income%2C%20I%20started%20writing%20a%20newsletter%20based%20on%20my%20lifelong%20experience%20with%20multiple%20mental%20illnesses%3A%20anxiety%2C%20depression%2C%20episodes%20of%20hypomania%2C%20and%20obsessive-compulsive%20disorder.%20Three%20years%20later%2C%20the%20newsletter%20continues%20to%20be%20my%20main%20livelihood.%20It%20has%20allowed%20me%20to%20spread%20awareness%20about%20mental%20illness%2C%20become%20part%20of%20a%20powerful%20global%20advocacy%20network%2C%20and%20access%20coveted%20career%20opportunities%2C%20including%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Freutersinstitute.politics.ox.ac.uk%2Fdollars-and-disparities-challenging-news-medias-coverage-global-mental-health-and-its-economics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efellowship%20at%20Oxford%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20ambition%20has%20come%20barging%20back%20into%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20repeatedly%20succumbed%20to%20the%20urge%20to%20do%20%3Cem%3Emore%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0hawk%20my%20work%20more%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eaggressively%2C%20reel%20in%20more%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Esubscribers%2C%20create%20more%20impact%20%E2%80%94%20despite%20a%20voice%20in%20my%20head%20warning%20me%20of%20the%20danger%20of%20sliding%20back%20into%20a%20dark%20space%2C%20reminding%20me%20that%20%3Cem%3Emore%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewill%20never%20be%20%3Cem%3Eenough%3C%2Fem%3E.%20There's%20a%20fine%20line%20between%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-find-career-ambition-stay-motivated-at-work-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emotivation%20needed%20to%20build%20a%20successful%20career%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20uncontrolled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-star-blackrock-manager-burnout-work-job-success-happiness-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eambition%20that%20ends%20in%20burnout%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20I%20unpacked%20this%20predicament%20in%20therapy%2C%20I%20began%20to%20wonder%3A%20How%20did%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-ive-stopped-telling-myself-to-be-more-ambitious-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eambition%20become%20such%20a%20force%20in%20our%20world%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20At%20what%20point%20does%20it%20turn%20on%20us%3F%20And%20is%20there%20a%20way%20out%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20ancient%20world%2C%20ambition%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20curse.%20The%20Roman%20philosophers%20Cicero%20and%20Seneca%20denounced%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bmalady%26quot%3B%20that%20preyed%20on%20%26quot%3Bthe%20greatest%20souls%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20William%20Casey%20King%20wrote%20in%20his%20book%20%26quot%3BAmbition%2C%20A%20History%3A%20From%20Vice%20to%20Virtue.%26quot%3B%20For%20centuries%20the%20desire%20for%20rank%2C%20fame%2C%20or%20power%20was%20abhorred%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bplague%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bcanker%20on%20the%20soul.%26quot%3B%20To%20be%20ambitious%20was%20to%20be%20a%20threat%20to%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20age%20of%20colonialism%2C%20ambition%20underwent%20a%20radical%20makeover%20as%20Western%20imperialists%20shrewdly%20created%20%26quot%3Bincentives%20to%20encourage%20potential%20emigrants%20to%20undertake%20colonization%2C%26quot%3B%20King%20wrote.%20Ambition%20was%20channeled%20toward%20civilizing%20the%20%26quot%3Buncivilized%26quot%3B%20and%20became%20a%20virtue%2C%20even%20as%20it%20legitimized%20oppression%20to%20devastating%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20isn't%20difficult%20to%20trace%20those%20roots%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20extractive%20capitalism%3A%20The%20ambitious%20entrepreneur%20sets%20out%20to%20%26quot%3Bmake%20the%20world%20a%20better%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20pursuit%20that%20paves%20the%20way%20for%20self-actualization%2C%20power%2C%20and%20wealth%20%E2%80%94%20and%20frequently%20leaves%20people%20and%20the%20planet%20as%20collateral%20damage.%20Winners%20don't%20quit.%20Keep%20calm%20and%20carry%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGranted%2C%20ambition%20has%20also%20driven%20people%20throughout%20history%20to%20challenge%20oppressive%20systems%2C%20but%20the%20%26quot%3Bonwards%20and%20upwards%26quot%3B%20narrative%20erases%20the%20reality%20that%20an%20individual's%20capacity%20for%20achieving%20success%20is%20shaped%20by%20factors%20far%20beyond%20their%20control.%20In%202018%2C%20across%20the%20world's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oecd.org%2Fstories%2Fsocial-mobility%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erichest%20countries%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20only%20about%20half%20of%2015-year-olds%20from%20households%20of%20low%20socioeconomic%20status%20said%20they%20expected%20to%20complete%20any%20kind%20of%20higher%20education%2C%20compared%20with%20more%20than%2080%25%20from%20high-status%20households%20who%20said%20the%20same.%20Children%20whose%20parents%20hold%20a%20college%20degree%20or%20the%20equivalent%20are%2045%20percentage%20points%20more%20likely%20to%20graduate%20from%20college%20than%20children%20whose%20parents%20earned%20less%20than%20a%20high-school%20degree%20or%20the%20equivalent.%20They're%20also%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20in%20good%20health%20and%20have%20more%20disposable%20income.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1007%2Fs10964-022-01721-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElsewhere%2C%20researchers%20have%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20children%20growing%20up%20in%20households%20reporting%20economic%20hardship%20are%20likely%20to%20perform%20worse%20in%20school%2C%20report%20having%20worse%20mental%20health%2C%20experience%20greater%20social%20isolation%2C%20and%20engage%20in%20more%20risky%20behavior%20relative%20to%20peers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20a%20pandemic%20to%20blow%20holes%20in%20the%20cult%20of%20ambition.%20In%202021%20and%202022%2C%20almost%20100%20million%20American%20workers%20left%20their%20jobs.%20Many%20who%20remained%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foverachievers-leaning-back-hustle-culture-coasting-employees-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equiet%20quit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20resolving%20to%20do%20no%20more%20than%20the%20bare%20minimum.%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20declared%20it%20the%20%26quot%3Bage%20of%20anti-ambition.%26quot%3B%20Time%20magazine%20announced%2C%20%26quot%3BAmbition%20is%20out.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BA%20bigger%20paycheck%3F%20I'd%20rather%20watch%20the%20sunset!%26quot%3B%20The%20Guardian%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreat-resignation-income-inequality-worker-employee-power-recession-company-control-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGreat%20Resignation%3C%2Fa%3E%20gave%20way%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquitting-job-big-stay-great-resignation-labor-market-economic-outlook-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBig%20Stay%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20Amid%20brutal%20mass%20layoffs%20and%20the%20ballooning%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20workers%20returned%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-hustle-generation-jobs-work-side-hustle-freelance-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehustling%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gobankingrates.com%2Fbanking%2Fbanks%2Fhow-much-money-do-americans-have-in-their-bank-accounts-in-2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20recent%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Americans%2C%20nearly%20half%20the%20respondents%20said%20they%20lived%20from%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck%20throughout%20the%20year.%20Over%20a%20third%20said%20they%20had%20less%20than%20%24100%20in%20their%20savings%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20driving%20many%20people%20back%20to%20the%20grind%20isn't%20ambition.%20It's%20survival.%20No%20wonder%20we%20can't%20let%20go%20of%20the%20hustle.%20We%20simply%20don't%20have%20the%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20born%20in%20the%20early%20'80s%20to%20a%20lower-middle-class%20family%20in%20a%20small%20industrial%20town%20in%20the%20east%20of%20India.%20It%20was%20India%20before%20the%20free%20market.%20Coca-Cola%20had%20been%20thrown%20out%20of%20the%20country%2C%20and%20color%20TVs%20were%20as%20exotic%20as%20flying%20saucers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20had%20survived%20extreme%20poverty%20before%20joining%20working-class%20occupations.%20I%20learned%20early%20in%20life%20that%20ambition%20wasn't%20just%20a%20personal%20trait%3B%20my%20family's%20salvation%20depended%20on%20it.%20Kids%20of%20our%20generation%20were%20raised%20to%20be%20devotees%20of%20upward%20mobility%2C%20usually%20by%20pursuing%20an%20engineering%20or%20medical%20degree.%20But%20I%20wanted%20to%20become%20a%20writer%2C%20which%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20recipe%20for%20starvation.%20My%20father%20was%20scared%20that%20I%20was%20heading%20for%20a%20hard%20life%20like%20he'd%20had%2C%20and%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20we%20barely%20talked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20I%20aced%20my%20high-school%20exams%2C%20my%20parents%20had%20a%20change%20of%20heart%20and%20decided%20to%20send%20me%20to%20India's%20most%20prestigious%20college%20to%20study%20English%20literature.%20They%20broke%20their%20backs%20so%20I%20could%20become%20the%20first%20person%20in%20my%20family%20to%20leave%20home%20and%20set%20foot%20in%20mythical%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%202001%20%E2%80%94%20exactly%20a%20decade%20into%20the%20liberalization%20of%20the%20Indian%20economy.%20Optimism%20was%20in%20the%20air.%20Malls%20and%20mobile%20phones%20were%20springing%20up%20everywhere%2C%20and%20Coke%20had%20come%20back.%20Ambition%20had%20leapt%20out%20of%20family%20conversations%20and%20turned%20into%20a%20national%20mission.%20Obscure%20terms%20like%20%26quot%3BGDP%20growth%26quot%3B%20were%20suddenly%20common%20as%20the%20country%20embraced%20upward%20mobility%2C%20encouraging%20the%20government%20to%20go%20into%20the%20next%20elections%20under%20the%20slogan%20%26quot%3BIndia%20Shining.%26quot%3B%20(It%20lost%20the%20elections%2C%20but%20that's%20a%20different%20story.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20college%20was%20the%20very%20cradle%20of%20ambition.%20My%20classmates%20were%20the%20children%20of%20ministers%20and%20bureaucrats%20%E2%80%94%20people%20who%20had%20%3Cem%3Emade%20it%3C%2Fem%3E.%20I%20couldn't%20relate%20to%20their%20exuberance%20and%20began%20hating%20everything%20about%20myself%3A%20my%20small-town%20accent%2C%20my%20unsculpted%20body%2C%20my%20unfashionable%20clothes%2C%20my%20ignorance%20of%20genteel%20etiquette.%20What%20started%20as%20culture%20shock%20metastasized%20into%20depression%20(though%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20name%20for%20it%20at%20the%20time).%20I%20felt%20lonely%20and%20lost%20in%20a%20world%20that%20had%20no%20patience%20for%20moping%2C%20but%20I%20learned%20to%20mask%20my%20feelings%20and%20blend%20in.%20I%20maintained%20a%20sparkling%20academic%20record%20while%20throwing%20myself%20into%20college%20clubs%20and%20societies.%20Few%20people%20had%20any%20clue%20that%20I%20was%20also%20routinely%20self-harming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20few%20years%20after%20earning%20my%20master's%20degree%2C%20I%20took%20whatever%20job%20paid%20decently%20so%20I%20could%20send%20money%20home.%20It%20was%20only%20after%20my%20family%20was%20financially%20stable%20that%20I%20joined%20the%20profession%20where%20my%20heart%20lay%3A%20journalism.%20I%20toiled%20hard%20and%20progressed%20rapidly%20to%20senior%20roles.%20I%20traveled%20the%20world%20and%20told%20important%20stories%20while%20pulling%2016-hour%20days%20in%20the%20name%20of%20passion%2C%20expertly%20covering%20up%20the%20torment%20within%20that%20never%20left%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20one%20day%2C%20I%20snapped.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-deal-with-stress-burnout-work-mental-health-professional-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBurnout%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20depression%20squeezed%20me%20like%20a%20ketchup%20sachet.%20I%20locked%20myself%20in%20a%20dark%20room%2C%20drowning%20in%20a%20cesspit%20of%20self-loathing%20and%20sheer%20fatigue.%20It%20took%20a%20brush%20with%20suicidality%20for%20me%20to%20finally%20seek%20clinical%20care.%20My%20ambition%20had%20helped%20me%20outrun%20the%20script%20I'd%20inherited%2C%20but%20at%20a%20hellish%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20blame%20ambition%20for%20all%20my%20troubles.%20As%20a%20cishet%2C%20upper-caste%2C%20English-speaking%20man%20with%20an%20elite%20education%2C%20I%20have%20been%20able%20to%20follow%20my%20ambition%20thanks%20to%20my%20enormous%20privilege.%20But%20I've%20also%20seen%20how%20allowing%20ambition%20to%20take%20over%20your%20life%20can%20mess%20with%20your%20sense%20of%20who%20you%20really%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sanitybytanmoy.com%2Fi-live-streamed-my-panic-attack-on%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emidnight%20panic-attack%20broadcast%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20a%20mental-health%20writer%2C%20I'm%20critical%20of%20predatory%20social-media%20platforms.%20But%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-avoid-burnout-as-an-entrepreneur-jim-mckelvey-block-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecreator%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20share%20my%20deeply%20personal%20struggles%20on%20these%20platforms%20because%20it%20has%20become%20my%20selling%20point.%20I%20often%20ask%20myself%3A%20Do%20I%20(over)share%20because%20I%20want%20to%20break%20taboos%2C%20or%20because%20it%20feeds%20my%20need%20for%20validation%20and%20helps%20me%20make%20a%20living%3F%20Is%20turning%20my%20illness%20into%20material%20for%20my%20work%20therapeutic%3F%20Or%20does%20it%20deliver%20me%20into%20the%20arms%20of%20the%20same%20toxic%20productivity%20culture%20that%20I%20rail%20against%20in%20my%20writing%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tension%20frequently%20pushes%20me%20into%20a%20tortured%20place.%20It%20doesn't%20help%20that%20I'm%20always%20wary%20of%20a%20relapse%20of%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sanitybytanmoy.com%2Fmood-stabiliser%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehypomania%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20condition%20characterized%20by%20abnormal%20energy%20with%20an%20exaggerated%20sense%20of%20self-confidence%20and%20creative%20ambition%2C%20often%20followed%20by%20exhaustion%2C%20overwhelm%2C%20and%20depression.%20It%20has%20become%20an%20untenable%20cycle%20that%20leaves%20me%20fantasizing%20about%20permanently%20breaking%20up%20with%20ambition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20plenty%20of%20research%20suggesting%20ambition%20can%20take%20a%20destructive%20turn.%20Chasing%20extrinsic%20goals%2C%20such%20as%20power%20and%20money%2C%20is%20a%20risk%20factor%20for%20depression.%20Unregulated%20ambition%20that%20can%20be%20satiated%20only%20by%20constant%20external%20validation%20is%20also%20sometimes%20associated%20with%20narcissistic%20personality%20disorder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20therapist%20assures%20me%20I%20don't%20fit%20that%20pathology%20(yet)%2C%20but%20I've%20learned%20to%20be%20mindful%20of%20how%20ambition%20can%20stem%20from%20deep%20inner%20wounds.%20Gabor%20Mat%C3%A9%2C%20an%20expert%20on%20addiction%20and%20trauma%2C%20says%20people%20who%20run%20themselves%20ragged%20in%20their%20professional%20lives%20are%20often%20acting%20out%20a%20childhood%20message%20that%20they're%20not%20good%20enough%20just%20as%20they%20are.%20They%20grow%20up%20needing%20to%20constantly%20prove%20they're%20worthy%20of%20love%20and%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMat%C3%A9's%20theory%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fgabor-mate-claims-trauma-contributes-to-everything-from-cancer-to-adhd-but-what-does-the-evidence-say-207144%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edetractors%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20other%20research%20has%20found%20that%20early-childhood%20adversity%20can%20dictate%20career%20choices%2C%20especially%20for%20people%20in%20%26quot%3Bhelping%20professions%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20healthcare%2C%20social%20work%2C%20and%20criminal%20justice.%20Some%20who%20venture%20into%20these%20careers%20are%20motivated%20by%20a%20desire%20to%20rescue%20others%20from%20the%20pain%20they%20themselves%20endured%2C%20even%20if%20it%20means%20putting%20themselves%20in%20harm's%20way.%20In%20his%20career%20construction%20theory%2C%20which%20offers%20a%20framework%20to%20explain%20why%20we%20choose%20the%20work%20we%20do%2C%20the%20psychologist%20Mark%20L.%20Savickas%20offers%20a%20striking%20insight%3A%20People%20seek%20to%20actively%20master%20what%20they%20passively%20suffer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frontiersin.org%2Farticles%2F10.3389%2Ffpsyg.2023.1108006%2Ffull%23ref36%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20linking%20ambition%20and%20%26quot%3Brelative%20deprivation%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20feeling%20that%20you've%20been%20treated%20unjustly%20compared%20with%20others%2C%20causing%20frustration%2C%20anger%2C%20and%20resentment.%20If%20you%20perceive%20yourself%20as%20overqualified%20for%20your%20job%2C%20you%20could%20be%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20relative%20deprivation%2C%20which%20could%20drive%20you%20to%20behave%20counterproductively%20and%20unethically%20at%20work.%20And%20the%20more%20ambitious%20you%20are%2C%20the%20greater%20your%20chance%20of%20falling%20into%20this%20negative%20loop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20peak%20of%20the%20Great%20Resignation%2C%20I%20came%20across%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F6224158%2Fambition-mental-health%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eguide%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20being%20ambitious%20without%20sacrificing%20your%20mental%20health.%20One%20of%20its%20key%20prescriptions%20was%20developing%20a%20growth%20mindset%2C%20or%20sidestepping%20external%20markers%20of%20success%20to%20find%20inner%2C%20personal%20growth.%20You%20could%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20learn%20a%20skill%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20it%20rather%20than%20for%20career%20gains.%20%26quot%3BHave%20you%20ever%20lost%20interest%20in%20a%20beloved%20hobby%20after%20turning%20it%20into%20a%20side%20hustle%3F%26quot%3B%20the%20guide%20asked%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20psychological%20satisfaction%20is%20your%20goal%2C%20you%20may%20be%20better%20off%20without%20the%20extra%20cash.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20want%20to%20write%20about%20mental%20health%20because%20I'm%20passionate%20about%20it.%20But%20I've%20come%20to%20depend%20on%20it%20for%20my%20livelihood%2C%20and%20that%20makes%20the%20work%20feel%20tainted.%20No%20wonder%20I've%20found%20my%20motivation%20sagging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExcept%20who%20in%20today's%20world%20can%20afford%20%26quot%3Binner%20growth%26quot%3B%20that%20warms%20the%20heart%20but%20leaves%20the%20kitchen%20cold%3F%20If%20you're%20one%20of%20the%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20who've%20recently%20been%20laid%20off%2C%20you%20aren't%20hustling%20to%20get%20ahead%20%E2%80%94%20you're%20hustling%20to%20find%20work%20that%20will%20keep%20the%20lights%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20made%20a%20decision.%20After%20decades%20of%20living%20in%20several%20of%20India's%20megalopolises%2C%20we%20moved%20to%20a%20small%20mountain%20town%20in%20the%20south%20of%20the%20country.%20I%20once%20scoffed%20at%20the%20idea%20of%20living%20close%20to%20nature%20as%20a%20first-world%20luxury%2C%20even%20though%20I%20experienced%20how%20urban%20pollution%20and%20noise%20can%20aggravate%20mental%20illness.%20But%20as%20parents%20to%20a%206-year-old%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20try%20a%20quieter%2C%20healthier%20lifestyle%2C%20even%20if%20it%20meant%20living%20far%20from%20regular%20employment%20opportunities%2C%20dipping%20into%20our%20savings%2C%20and%20paring%20down%20our%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sanitybytanmoy.com%2Fthe-happy-death-of-ambition%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20mountains%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there's%20no%20dust%20and%20noise.%20The%20internet%20is%20fickle%2C%20but%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20years%20I%20feel%20connected%20with%20my%20neighbors.%20My%20relationship%20with%20ambition%20is%20healing%3A%20I%20still%20go%20on%20Instagram%20and%20tell%20my%20story%2C%20but%20I've%20discovered%20that%20filming%20myself%20while%20looking%20out%20at%20the%20hills%20is%20far%20less%20likely%20to%20trigger%20a%20panic%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Ftanmoy-goswami%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ETanmoy%20Goswami%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20user-survivor%20and%20creator%20of%20Sanity%2C%20an%20independent%2C%20reader-funded%20mental-health-storytelling%20platform.%20He%20is%20a%20past%20fellow%20of%20the%20Reuters%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20Journalism%2C%20University%20of%20Oxford.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fambition-breakup-burnout-depression-anxiety-pandemic-layoffs-creator-economy-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710408841000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ef5c10ce7f1785b2e88f30%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fambition-breakup-burnout-depression-anxiety-pandemic-layoffs-creator-economy-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%20drive%20to%20succeed%20helped%20lift%20me%20out%20of%20the%20lower-middle%20class.%20But%20it%20came%20at%20a%20terrible%20price.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Tanmoy%20Goswami)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fambition-breakup-burnout-depression-anxiety-pandemic-layoffs-creator-economy-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Giant%20volcano%20spanning%20a%20whopping%20280%20miles%20discovered%20on%20Mars%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710408780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F03%2F70x70%2Fskynews-mars-volcano-nasa-spa