ogy%20than%20white%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20a%202022%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.technologyreview.com%2F2022%2F12%2F06%2F1064287%2Fubers-facial-recognition-is-locking-indian-drivers-out-of-their-accounts%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%20by%20the%20MIT%20Technology%20Review%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20Uber's%20facial%20recognition%20feature%20%E2%80%94%20used%20for%20identity%20verification%2C%20similar%20to%20Spark%20%E2%80%94%20could%20have%20misidentified%20drivers%20in%20India%2C%20partly%20because%20AI%20models%20aren't%20as%20well-trained%20on%20South%20Asian%20faces%20as%20white%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20suggested%20that%20a%20simple%20appearance%20change%20like%20growing%20a%20beard%20could%20prevent%20the%20tech%20from%20detecting%20someone's%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFacial%20recognition%20developers%20say%20mistakes%20are%20possible%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20that%20appears%20to%20have%20stopped%20the%20tech%20from%20rolling%20out%20to%20new%20places.%20Major%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvornado-landlord-using-facial-recognition-buildings-nyc-office-portfolio-biometrics-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elandlords%20have%20added%20the%20tech%20to%20office%20buildings%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20workers%20have%20returned%20to%20offices%2C%20for%20instance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirline%20passengers%20can%20encounter%20facial%20recognition%20at%20multiple%20points%20in%20an%20airport%2C%20from%20the%20security%20line%20to%20customs%20and%20passport%20control%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F02%2F18%2Ftravel%2Ffacial-recognition-airports-biometrics.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520the%2520United%2520States%252C%2520major%2Ckiosks%2520at%2520immigration%2520and%2520customs.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalmart%20worked%20with%20a%20company%20called%20Persona%20to%20add%20facial%20recognition%20to%20its%20Spark%20app.%20While%20Persona's%20website%20doesn't%20specifically%20mention%20trouble%20identifying%20people%20of%20color%2C%20it%20does%20acknowledge%20that%20the%20tech%20has%20pitfalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20example%2C%20someone's%20eyeglasses%20may%20fool%20the%20system%20into%20thinking%20it's%20a%20reflection%20on%20a%20screen%2C%20or%20a%20low-resolution%20photo%20may%20trick%20the%20system%20into%20thinking%20it's%20a%20digital%20replay%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwithpersona.com%2Fblog%2Fwhat-is-selfie-identity-verification-and-how-does-it-work%3Futm_audience%3Da%26utm_term%3Dpersona%2520verification%26utm_campaign%3Dacq_us_generic_branded-123153801337%26utm_source%3Dgoogle%26utm_medium%3Dppc%26hsa_acc%3D5817921572%26hsa_cam%3D14055031618%26hsa_grp%3D123153801337%26hsa_ad%3D686889489575%26hsa_src%3Dg%26hsa_tgt%3Dkwd-1392945550753%26hsa_kw%3Dpersona%2520verification%26hsa_mt%3Db%26hsa_net%3Dadwords%26hsa_ver%3D3%26gad_source%3D1%26gclid%3DCj0KCQjw-r-vBhC-ARIsAGgUO2CFDmye7xU8QCIlVR_3nE7chlcyamLJjLdgXN2ylOFy2rJQl2yh6eUaAsboEALw_wcB%23toc-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eits%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20shortcomings%20may%20increase%20the%20risk%20of%20false%20negatives%20during%20the%20verification%20process%2C%20which%20may%20result%20in%20legitimate%20users%20being%20denied%20verification%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20continues.%20Persona%20and%20Walmart%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20BI's%20requests%20for%20information%20about%20the%20technology%20or%20partnership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20TSA%20and%20CBP%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20BI.%20A%20TSA%20spokesperson%20told%20the%20New%20York%20Times%20in%20February%20that%20halting%20biometric%20technology%20like%20facial%20recognition%20would%20%26quot%3Btake%20us%20back%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20did%20not%20specifically%20address%20the%20racial%20disparity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERetailers'%20attempts%20to%20use%20facial%20recognition%20to%20catch%20shoplifters%20haven't%20gone%20well.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20it's%20possible%20to%20opt%20out%20of%20using%20facial%20recognition%20technology%20%E2%80%94%20and%20its%20high%20error%20rate.%20If%20getting%20on%20your%20next%20flight%20involves%20scanning%20your%20face%20instead%20of%20a%20boarding%20pass%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20gate%20agent%20is%20supposed%20to%20offer%20you%20a%20manual%20check%20of%20your%20ID%20and%20pass%20instead%2C%20according%20to%20CBP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20sidestepping%20facial%20recognition%20often%20isn't%20possible%2C%20said%20Gideon%20Christian%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Calgary%20who%20has%20written%20about%20the%20legal%20and%20societal%20aspects%20of%20facial%20recognition%20technology.%20He%20pointed%20to%20some%20retailers'%20decision%20to%20use%20the%20tech%20in%20their%20stores%20to%20catch%20shoplifters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ftc.gov%2Fnews-events%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2F2023%2F12%2Frite-aid-banned-using-ai-facial-recognition-after-ftc-says-retailer-deployed-technology-without%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFTC%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20drugstore%20chain%20Rite%20Aid%20had%20improperly%20used%20facial%20recognition%20technology%20in%20%26quot%3Bhundreds%20of%20stores%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20detriment%20of%20women%20and%20people%20of%20color.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERite%20Aid's%20use%20of%20facial%20recognition%20technology%20%26quot%3Bleft%20its%20customers%20facing%20humiliation%20and%20other%20harms%2C%20and%20its%20order%20violations%20put%20consumers'%20sensitive%20information%20at%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20Samuel%20Levine%2C%20the%20FTC's%20Bureau%20of%20Consumer%20Protection%20director%2C%20said%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FTC%20banned%20Rite%20Aid%20from%20using%20facial%20recognition%20technology%20in%20stores%20for%20five%20years%20as%20a%20result.%20Rite%20Aid%20accepted%20the%20settlement%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.riteaid.com%2Fpress-releases%2Fpress-release-details%2F2023%2FRite-Aid-Reaches-Settlement-with-FTC%2Fdefault.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisputed%20the%20FTC's%20allegations%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20how%20and%20where%20it%20used%20facial%20recognition%20%E2%80%94%20the%20company%20said%20it%20only%20tested%20the%20tech%20in%20%26quot%3Ba%20limited%20number%20of%20stores%2C%26quot%3B%20for%20instance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFacial%20recognition's%20racial%20bias%20is%20the%20same%20bias%20that%20black%20people%20already%20experience%20when%20they%20go%20shopping%2C%20Christian%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20basically%20have%20facial%20recognition%20technology%20basically%20making%20the%20same%20baseless%20allegation%2C%20because%20the%20face%20matches%20with%20some%20other%20individual%20in%20the%20database%20and%20then%20triggers%20alerts%2C%26quot%3B%20Christian%20said%20in%20an%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChristian%20told%20BI%20that%20its%20lack%20of%20privacy%20and%20its%20accuracy%20issues%20should%20be%20enough%20reason%20to%20roll%20back%20its%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20not%20think%20it's%20appropriate%20for%20us%20to%20violate%20the%20fundamental%20right%20of%20every%20person%20walking%20into%20a%20retail%20store%20just%20because%20we%20want%20to%20catch%20a%20few%20shoplifters%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20work%20for%20Walmart%20Spark%2C%20Instacart%2C%20DoorDash%2C%20or%20another%20gig%20delivery%20service%20and%20have%20a%20story%20idea%20to%20share%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20abitter%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-facial-recognition-technology-might-not-recognize-you-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710406801000%2C