2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14115722%2FUntitled-design-40-1.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20notification%20of%20rules%20for%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20(CAA)%20has%20invited%20severe%20criticism%20from%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20Amnesty%20International.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalling%20it%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fus-and-un-express-concern-about-caa%2Famp_articleshow%2F108443961.cms%5C%22%3Efundamentally%20discriminatory%20in%20nature%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9C%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20of%20the%20Office%20of%20the%20UN%20High%20Commissioner%20for%20Human%20Rights%20told%20Reuters%2C%20%E2%80%9CAs%20we%20said%20in%202019%2C%20we%20are%20concerned%20that%20CAA%20is%20fundamentally%20discriminatory%20in%20nature%20and%20in%20breach%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20international%20human%20rights%20obligations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20official%20added%20that%20his%20office%20was%20studying%20whether%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20law%20complies%20with%20international%20human%20rights%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20United%20States%20expressed%20concerns.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20concerned%20about%20the%20notification%20of%20CAA%20on%20March%2011.%20We%20are%20closely%20monitoring%20how%20this%20act%20will%20be%20implemented%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20state%20department%20spokesperson%20told%20Reuters%20separately.%20%E2%80%9CRespect%20for%20religious%20freedom%20and%20equal%20treatment%20under%20the%20law%20for%20all%20communities%20are%20fundamental%20democratic%20principles%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20spokesperson%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Amnesty%20International%20said%20the%20operationalisation%20of%20the%20CAA%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cblow%20to%20the%20Indian%20constitutional%20values%20of%20equality%20and%20religious%20non-discrimination%20and%20inconsistent%20and%20incompatible%20with%20India%E2%80%99s%20international%20human%20rights%20obligations%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20is%20a%20bigoted%20law%20that%20legitimises%20discrimination%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20religion%20and%20should%20never%20have%20been%20enacted%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20Its%20operationalization%20is%20a%20poor%20reflection%20on%20the%20Indian%20authorities%20as%20they%20fail%20to%20listen%20to%20a%20multitude%20of%20voices%20critical%20of%20the%20CAA%20%E2%80%93%20from%20people%20across%20the%20country%2C%20civil%20society%2C%20international%20human%20rights%20organizations%20and%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Aakar%20Patel%2C%20chair%20of%20the%20board%20at%20Amnesty%20International%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFour%20years%20after%20the%20contentious%20Citizenship%20(Amendment)%20Act%20(CAA)%20was%20enacted%2C%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20on%20Monday%2C%20March%2011%2C%20notified%20necessary%20rules%20for%20the%20law%20to%20be%20implemented.%20Without%20rules%20being%20framed%2C%20the%20Act%20could%20not%20be%20implemented.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CAA%20aims%20to%20provide%20citizenship%20to%20Hindus%2C%20Parsis%2C%20Sikhs%2C%20Buddhists%2C%20Jains%20and%20Christians%20purportedly%20fleeing%20persecution%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20Muslim-majority%20neighbours%20%E2%80%93%20namely%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20Afghanistan%20and%20Bangladesh%20%E2%80%93%20and%20who%20arrived%20in%20India%20before%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20exclusion%20of%20Muslims%20from%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20legislation%20and%20fears%20that%20it%20would%20disenfranchise%20many%20Muslims%20in%20India%20when%20combined%20with%20the%20National%20Register%20of%20Citizens%20(NRC)%20had%20drawn%20widespread%20protests%20from%20thousands%20of%20citizens%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20protests%20and%20violence%20that%20ensued%2C%20the%20government%20notified%20the%20law%20in%20December%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710398394000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14115722%2FUntitled-design-40-1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdiscriminatory-in-nature-un-us-amnesty-international-slam-caa-rules%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Four%20years%20after%20the%20contentious%20Citizenship%20(Amendment)%20Act%20(CAA)%20was%20enacted%2C%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20on%20Monday%2C%20March%2011%2C%20notified%20necessary%20rules%20for%20the%20law%20to%20be%20implemented.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdiscriminatory-in-nature-un-us-amnesty-international-slam-caa-rules%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UK%20Cracks%20Down%3A%20Foreign%20Governments%20Barred%20From%20Owning%20Newspapers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20British%20government%20announced%20plans%20to%20ban%20foreign%20governments%20from%20owning%20newspapers%20and%20magazines%20in%20the%20UK.%20This%20move%20comes%20amid%20controversy%20surrounding%20a%20proposed%20takeover%20of%20the%20Daily%20Telegraph%20and%20Spectator%20by%20a%20United%20Arab%20Emirates-backed%20firm%2C%20RedBird%20IMI%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20BBC%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20legislation%2C%20introduced%20as%20an%20amendment%20to%20the%20Digital%20Markets%20Act%20currently%20in%20Parliament%2C%20aims%20to%20safeguard%20a%20free%20press.%20Critics%20of%20the%20Telegraph%20deal%20expressed%20concerns%20about%20foreign%20government%20influence%20on%20British%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20ban%20would%20effectively%20block%20the%20current%20takeover%20bid%20by%20RedBird%20IMI%2C%20forcing%20them%20to%20restructure%20their%20ownership%20if%20they%20wish%20to%20proceed.%20Foreign%20individuals%20and%20private%20companies%20will%20still%20be%20allowed%20to%20own%20British%20publications%20unde